<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n36126f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36126f">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36126f"> 126(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <span class="strike"><span class="striketext">N</span></span> <span class="strike"><span class="striketext">Lammath</span></span> Lammas Day</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">On <mark>Lammas Day</mark> (August 13th), if you get up early, you may meet the herdsman as he leads the cattle all afield together &ldquo;under the opening eyelids of the morn.&rdquo; They make for the stubbles then, but after All Saints&apos; they must use one or other of the green commons, according to the season. <small> Reginald L. Hine, <a name="RLHH" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#RLHH"><cite title="source">The History of Hitchin</cite></a>, Vol. I. (Nov 1929) 24</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: IX.A.2-1: &ldquo;Lammas Day (August 13th)&rdquo; </mm> </dd></dl>
